definitions.definition: ( linear algebra ) The matrix derived from performing a transpose operation on a given matrix.
( graph theory ) A graph whose every edge has had its direction reversed.

main_definition: ( linear algebra ) The matrix derived from performing a transpose operation on a given matrix.
secondary_definitions: ( graph theory ) A graph whose every edge has had its direction reversed.

definitions.definition: The process of rearranging elements in a matrix , by interchanging their respective row and column positional indicators.

main_definition: ( linear algebra ) The process of rearranging elements in a matrix , by interchanging their respective row and column positional indicators.
